Reasoning: The paper focuses on investigating the ability of the FiLM model to learn various linguistic constructions, which falls under the natural language processing (NLP) domain. Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. Additionally, the FiLM model is a deep learning model, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.LG (Machine Learning), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) sub-categories. Finally, the CLEVR dataset used in the paper is an image-based dataset, which could also place the paper under the cs.CV (Computer Vision) sub-category.
